We are excited to announce that Ms. Rachel Beach has joined the Canton College Prep staff as a K-2 teacher! In her words, "My name is Rachel Beach and I live in Canton. I am beyond excited for my first year teaching at Canton College Prep! I graduated from Mount Union in 2016 and I have a B.A in Early Childhood Education. I love being with friends and family. Lastly, I love to run, read, and everything Disney!"

Please take a moment to welcome Ms. Beach to the team!

post_text:
We are excited to announce that Ms. Kim Adkins has joined the Canton College Prep staff as an Intervention Specialist! In her words, "I am originally from Canton, Ohio and currently live in Akron. I obtained my Bachelor of Arts in General Studies from Kent State University with a minor in Education and Psychology. I also earned a Master of Arts in Education degree from Walsh University, and later obtained my Intervention Specialist K-12 license from Notre Dame College, South Euclid campus. I have been an IS for 5 years at St. Robert and William Catholic School in Euclid and for Akron Public Schools. I believe that educating our youth with the necessary tools needed to be successful is essential to society."

Please take a moment to welcome Ms. Adkins to the team!

post_text:
Spartan families,

Thank you for your patience as we finalize our plans for the closure that was communicated by Governor Mike DeWine today. School will be in session on Friday, 3/13, but closed for scholars on Monday, 3/16 through Friday, 4/3. Parents and scholars are encouraged to gather any supplies needed for the break tomorrow during normal school hours.

We will remain in communication with you throughout the break through social media as well as our school messaging system. Please ensure that your contact information is updated in the main office so you do not miss any important announcements or updates about accessing work for your scholar.

Please stay informed, and stay safe during this unprecedented time.

-Principal Lindsay

We will have maintenance crews scrub the school from top to bottom during the closure to help avoid the spread of illness during the flu season. If your child is sick, please take them to a doctor and keep them home to rest so they may return to school on Tuesday, January 28th. Thank you!

post_text: We are excited to announce that ESGR State Committees awarded Canton College Prep with the "Above and Beyond Award" for going above and beyond the legal requirements and providing our Guard and Reserve employees additional, non-mandated benefits. The award is given in limited numbers by the state of Ohio. After being nominated by Mr. Zachary Penrod, Canton College Prep is the only school in the state of Ohio to earn such an award. Thank you for the nomination and for your service, Mr. Penrod!

post_text: Sending a HUGE shout out to Ms. Simon for being recognized by the Ohio Council of Community Schools for her accomplishments!
shared_text:
Ohio Council of Community Schools
May 14, 2019 at 10:10 AM ·

Happy National #CharterSchoolsWeek!
Today we're highlighting some of the amazing teachers in our schools.
Emily Simon is a third grade teacher at Canton College Preparatory School. Ms. Simon was a founding teacher when the school first opened in 2013 and is now in her 6th year.
During those six years, Ms. Simon has been a phenomenal teacher! In the 2017-2018 school year, 93.1% of her scholars met the 3rd Grade Reading Guarantee requirements for promotion to the 4th Grade!
Not only is she a wonderful teacher, but she also serves in a leadership capacity. Ms. Simon is also Canton College Preparatory School's school-based RESA mentor for teachers progressing through the Resident Educator program.

Thank you Ms. Simon for all you do for the students at Canton College Preparatory School!
